===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*preh₂-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|for}}, from {{inh|en|ang|for||for, because of}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*furi||for}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*preh₂-}}.

Cognate with {{cog|fy|foar||for}}, {{cog|nl|voor||for}}, {{cog|de|für||for}}, {{cog|da|for||for}}, {{cog|sv|för||for}}, {{cog|no|for||for}}, {{cog|is|fyrir||for}}, {{cog|la|per||by, through, for, by means of}} and Romance language descendants (e.g. {{cog|es|por||for}}), {{cog|grc|περί||for, about, toward}}, {{cog|lt|per||by, through, during}}, {{cog|sk|pre||for}}, {{cog|sa|परि||over, around|tr=pári}}.

