#*: {{quote|ang|Þa wurdon hi ealle þurh þæt wundor ablicgede and þæs þægnes gebedda ðe þa gebroþra heold wæs '''for''' six gearum for swiðlicre untrumnysse...|Then they were all astonished at that miracle; and the wife of the officer, who had charge of the brothers, '''for''' six years, through a severe sickness...}}
# {{l|en|for}} (for the [[sake]] of) ''(+ dative)''
#* '''c. 990''', ''{{w|Wessex Gospels}}'', [https://archive.org/stream/dahalgangodspelo00thor#page/n145/mode/2up Luke 9:24]
#*: {{quote|ang|Sē þe his sāwle '''for''' mē forspilþ, hē hīe ġehǣlþ.|Whoever destroys their soul '''for''' me will save it.}}
# {{l|en|for}} (on behalf of, instead of) ''(+ accusative)''
#* '''c. 992''', [[w:Ælfric of Eynsham|Ælfric]], "[https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Homilies_of_the_Anglo-Saxon_Church/XXVII The Nativity of St. Paul the Apostle]"
#*: {{quote|ang|Petrus āna spræc '''for''' ealne þone hēap.|Paul by himself spoke '''for''' the whole group.}}
# [[ago]] ''(+ dative)''
#: {{ux|ang|Hē swealt '''for''' swelċe... twām þūsendum ġēara.|He died like... two thousand years '''ago'''.}}
#* '''c. 995''', [[w:Ælfric of Eynsham|Ælfric]], [https://archive.org/stream/grammatik00aelfuoft#page/n12/mode/2up ''Extracts on Grammar in English'']
#*: {{quote|ang|Is nū for þȳ Godes þēowum and mynstermannum ġeorne tō wearnienne þæt sēo hālġe lār on ūrum dagum ne ācōliġe oþþe ātēoriġe swā swā hit wæs ġedōn on Angelcynne nū '''for''' ānum fēawum gēarum, swā þæt nān Englisċ prēost ne cūðe dihtan oþþe āsmēaġan ānne pistol on Lǣden, oþ þæt Dūnstān ærċebisċop and Æðelwold bisċop eft þā lāre on munuclīfum ārǣrdon.|That's why God's servants and monks should be very careful not to let this sacred learning cool or fade in our time, the way it did in England a few years '''ago''', when none of our priests could compose or interpret a letter in Latin, until archbishop Dunstan and bishop Æthelwold revived learning in monastic life.}}
# (Usually in the phrase ''for [[eall]]'') {{l|en|for all}}, {{l|en|despite}}, {{l|en|in spite of}} ''(+ dative)''
#: {{ux|ang|Hēo swealt on fefre '''for''' eallum hire dǣdum.|She died of a fever, '''despite''' all her deeds.}}

